Thursday Sector Laggards: Materials, Industrial


July 20, 2017, 02:32:47 PM EDT
By MarketNewsVideo.com, BNK Invest









































Shutterstock photo


Looking at the sectors faring worst as of midday Thursday, shares of Materials companies are underperforming other sectors, showing a 0.9% loss. Within that group, PPG Industries Inc (Symbol: PPG) and Mohawk Industries, Inc. (Symbol: MHK) are two of the day's laggards, showing a loss of 6.3% and 2.2%, respectively. Among the high volume ETFs  , one ETF closely following materials stocks is the Materials Select Sector SPDR ETF (Symbol: XLB), which is down 0.8% on the day, and up 11.88% year-to-date. PPG Industries Inc, meanwhile, is up 13.17% year-to-date, and Mohawk Industries, Inc. is up 21.38% year-to-date. PPG makes up approximately 4.6% of the underlying holdings of XLB. The next worst performing sector is the Industrial sector, showing a 0.5% loss. Among large Industrial stocks, Alliance Data Systems Corp. (Symbol: ADS) and C.H. Robinson Worldwide, Inc. (Symbol: CHRW) are the most notable, showing a loss of 9.4% and 5.1%, respectively. One ETF closely tracking Industrial stocks is the Industrial Select Sector SPDR ETF ( XLI  ), which is down 0.5% in midday trading, and up 11.82% on a year-to-date basis. Alliance Data Systems Corp., meanwhile, is up 4.92% year-to-date, and C.H. Robinson Worldwide, Inc., is down 9.81% year-to-date. CHRW makes up approximately 0.4% of the underlying holdings of XLI.    Comparing these stocks and ETFs on a trailing twelve month basis, below is a relative stock price performance chart, with each of the symbols shown in a different color as labeled in the legend at the bottom:         Here's a snapshot of how the S&P 500 components within the various sectors are faring in afternoon trading on Thursday. As you can see, five sectors are up on the day, while three sectors are down.     Sector % Change  Healthcare +0.7%   Utilities +0.5%   Services +0.4%   Technology & Communications +0.2%   Consumer Products +0.1%   Financial -0.0%   Energy -0.1%   Industrial -0.5%   Materials -0.9%     25 Dividend Giants Widely Held By ETFs Â» 



